If you want to build a Windows LAN chat application similar to **IP Messenger**, you can start with a fairly simple architecture.

## How IP Messenger Works

On the same LAN:

1. User A opens the application.
2. App broadcasts its presence to the network.
3. User B receives the broadcast and appears in the user list.
4. Users send messages directly using TCP/UDP sockets.
5. No internet or central server is required.

