## Architecture

```text
+------------------+
| User A           |
| 192.168.1.10     |
+--------+---------+
         |
         | LAN
         |
+--------+---------+
| User B           |
| 192.168.1.11     |
+------------------+
```

### Discovery

Use UDP Broadcast:

```python
sock.sendto(
    b"HELLO",
    ('255.255.255.255', 5000)
)
```

Every client listens on port 5000:

```python
sock.bind(('', 5000))
```

When a HELLO packet arrives:

```python
HELLO|Nandan-PC
```

Add that user to the online list.

---

## Messaging

Use TCP for reliable message delivery.

### Server Thread

```python
server.bind(("0.0.0.0", 6000))
server.listen()
```

### Send Message

```python
client.connect(("192.168.1.11", 6000))
client.send(message.encode())
```

